  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>When you draw a foe's blood in combat, that creature begins to doubt its skills.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Int 13; Bluff, Diplomacy, and Intimidate 5 ranks.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>As a full-round action, you can diminish the confidence of a creature you've dealt damage to within the last minute. That creature must succeed at a Will save or take a -6 penalty on skill checks for one of the following skills of your choice: Bluff, Diplomacy, or Intimidate. This ability lasts until the subject is healed of all hit point damage, up to a maximum of 1 hour.<br/><br/><b>Special</b><br/>A shaman or witch with this blood hex can use it as a standard action. Additionally, if a shaman or witch uses this blood hex, the target takes the penalty on Bluff, Diplomacy, and Intimidate checks.",
